{
  "number": 1061,
  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/1061",
  "title": "Allow to preselect refinements",
  "body": "For all refinement widgets, it should be easy to automatically select refinements at start.\n\nFor example, with a menu, I should be able to say that the facet value \"iphone\" is selected by default.\n\nWe have had numerous users willing to do so previously and the answer we had was to use the \"searchParameters\".\n\nUnfortunately there's no easy way for our users to know which searchParameters to use and what's their format given their widget.\n\nEven if we would document it, it would look weird to have to provide a \"hierarchicalRefinements: {}\" because you want to preselect menu items (yes, internally menu is a one level hierarchicalRefinement).\n\nSome of our widgets actually already implement that sort of things, like passing \"min\" and \"max\" to the rangeSlider: it defines the numeric refinement to apply.\n\nSo it needs to be a new API entry at the widgets level.\n",
